oai_dc:dc.dc:title: der Vogelfanger: FOREST EDGE GARDEN
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Griffith, Joseph G.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Many people envision the tropical rainforestas full of large leaved lush plants.When looking at a typical rainforest, it issurprising how few large leaved plantsthere are. The northern counterpart of arainforest is the temperate hardwoodforest and the lushest and most diversepart of it (as with a rainforest) is theforest edge. Here, sunlight penetrates tothe ground. As a result, there are trees,shrubs, annuals, and perennials, bulbs andgrasses.
